title: For Sale:  Remington Defense XM110 SASS
postcontent: Remington Defense XM110 SASS prototype (Semi-Automatic Sniper System). This rifle was one of the designs that Remington Defense submitted for the Military SASS trials. This is a very nice unfired .308/7.62 Nato AR-10 style rifle meant to replace the Remington M24 sniper rifle. The US Military opened up SASS trials to all manufactures that built precision AR-10 style rifles. Like Remington Defense, FN, DPMS, KAC, etc. When the Military decided to postpone the winning rifle KAC filed a law suit against the US Military Department. The sniper choice of summited rifles Was the Remington XM110 because of it's reliability. The Knights rifle was a bit more accurate but reliability issued ensued because of such tight tolerances. In the end they selected the Knights Armament rifle. This is not only a collector piece but a shooter as well and it will only go up in value as the years go by. Truly an investment. Mounted on this rifle is a Leupold Military Mark 4 34mm tube 6.5-20x50 in Mark 8 34mm mount. This is what was used in the trials and is an awesome sniper rifle and optic setup.
